c=\cos
s=\sin
\frac{2s}{1+2c}=\frac {\sqrt{3}} 2
2s=\frac{\sqrt{3}}2+c\times\sqrt{3}
2s-\sqrt{3}\times c=\frac{\sqrt3}2
\frac{2\sin x}{1+2\cos x} = \frac{\sqrt{3}}2,
\implies \frac{4t}{1+t^2+2(1-t^2)}= \frac{\sqrt{3}}2 \implies \sqrt3t^2+8t-3\sqrt3=0
\implies t=\frac{-8\pm\sqrt{8^2-4\sqrt3(-3\sqrt3)}}{2\sqrt3}
0<x<180^\circ,0<x<90^\circ\implies \tan \frac x2>0 
t=-3\sqrt3\implies \tan \frac x2=-3\sqrt3<0
t=\frac1{\sqrt3}\implies \tan \frac x2=\frac1{\sqrt3}=\tan30^\circ
\implies  \frac x2=180^\circ n+30^\circ
